[Posting all of these cases of EEE is really sad. People have not heeded the warnings of those in public health. When the mosquitos were testing positive for EEE, people should have been vaccinating the horses.

Even if the cities/counties/parishes were not testing the mosquitoes, vaccines to protect your horse is part of the responsibility of owning and caring for animals.

Please get your animal vaccinated. It is not too late, as this could be a long EEE season. Please use sprays/repellents against flies/mosquitoes approved for horses. Keep fans running in the barn to discourage mosquitoes and flies. - Mod.TG

